          "Now compute $\\sin^{2}B+\\sin^{2}C-2\\cos A\\cos B\\cos C=\\sin^{2}B+\\sin^{2}C-2\\sin B\\sin C\\cos B\\cos C+2\\cos^{2}B\\cos^{2}C.$",
          "Write $\\sin^{2}B+\\sin^{2}C=(1-\\cos^{2}B)+(1-\\cos^{2}C)$ and regroup: the expression becomes $2-\\big(\\cos^{2}B+\\cos^{2}C-2\\cos^{2}B\\cos^{2}C\\big)-2\\sin B\\sin C\\cos B\\cos C.$ Using $\\cos^{2}B+\\cos^{2}C-2\\cos^2 B\\cos^2 C=\\cos^{2}B(1-\\cos^2 C)+\\cos^2 C(1-\\cos^2 B)=\\cos^2 B\\sin^2 C+\\cos^2 C\\sin^2 B$, this is $2-\\big(\\cos B\\sin C+\\cos C\\sin B\\big)^{2}=2-\\sin^{2}(B+C)=2-\\sin^{2}A.$",
          "Adding the remaining $\\sin^{2}A$ from $F$ gives $F=\\sin^{2}A+\\big(2-\\sin^{2}A\\big)=2$ identically, so $F$ is constant $=2$, proving (a) with no special identity invoked.",
          "Part (b) then follows exactly as before: $\\sin^{2}A+\\sin^{2}B+\\sin^{2}C=2+2\\cos A\\cos B\\cos C$, and since $\\cos A\\cos B\\cos C\\le\\tfrac18$ with equality at the equilateral triangle, the maximum is $\\boxed{\\tfrac94}$ at $A=B=C=\\tfrac\\pi3$."
