          "At $k=\\sqrt2$ the quadratic $(1+\\sqrt2)x^{2}-2x+(\\sqrt2-1)=0$ has the double root $x=\\dfrac{2}{2(1+\\sqrt2)}=\\dfrac{1}{1+\\sqrt2}=\\sqrt2-1$. Hence the maximum $\\sqrt2$ is attained only at $\\boxed{x=\\sqrt2-1}$."
