          "Thus $\\cos A+\\cos B+\\cos C=1+2\\sin\\tfrac{C}{2}\\cos\\tfrac{A-B}{2}-2\\sin^2\\tfrac{C}{2}$. Set $t=\\sin\\tfrac{C}{2}\\in(0,1)$ and $p=\\cos\\tfrac{A-B}{2}\\in(0,1]$; the expression is $1+2pt-2t^2$.",
          "Complete the square: $1+2pt-2t^2=1+\\dfrac{p^2}{2}-2\\Big(t-\\dfrac{p}{2}\\Big)^2\\le 1+\\dfrac{p^2}{2}\\le 1+\\dfrac12=\\dfrac32$, since $\\big(t-\\tfrac{p}{2}\\big)^2\\ge0$ and $p\\le1$. No concavity assumption is used, so the bound holds for obtuse triangles too.",
          "Equality forces $t=\\tfrac{p}{2}$ and $p=1$: from $p=1$ we get $A=B$, and then $t=\\tfrac12$ means $\\sin\\tfrac{C}{2}=\\tfrac12$, i.e. $C=\\tfrac{\\pi}{3}$, whence $A=B=C=\\tfrac{\\pi}{3}$.",
          "Therefore $\\cos A+\\cos B+\\cos C\\le\\dfrac32$ with equality only for the equilateral triangle, and the maximum is $\\boxed{\\dfrac32}$."
