          "Form the gap to $\\tfrac32$: a direct expansion shows $\\dfrac32-(\\cos A+\\cos B+\\cos C)=\\dfrac{a^3+b^3+c^3+3abc-a^2(b+c)-b^2(c+a)-c^2(a+b)}{2abc}$.",
          "The numerator is precisely Schur's expression $a(a-b)(a-c)+b(b-a)(b-c)+c(c-a)(c-b)$, which is $\\ge0$ for all nonnegative $a,b,c$ (Schur, exponent $t=1$). Since $a,b,c>0$, the whole fraction is $\\ge0$.",
          "Hence $\\cos A+\\cos B+\\cos C\\le\\dfrac32$ for every triangle, with no convexity used anywhere.",
